content.description:
Multiple starts can be done with this one(and any of them for that reason)

Start in the dihedral and move to the slopey crimp about 4 feet up. Big moves to the right bring you to good jugs. Throw up a heel or whatever and grab the fat horn at the end and top out
content.location: start in the dihedral or the underlcing at the very right of the boulder

content.description:
Start in the undercling and crimp about 3 feet up. Slap to some slopers around the lip and friction your way up and over the bulge.

Great little problem, and the sit start will bump it up a notch for sure.

Originally done from the sit, and goes at about v5
content.protection: Just a pad will be fine
content.location: The very left of the boulder. Obvious starting holds, and you'll be able to identify the good slopers to slap to by the lack of black patina on the rock.

content.description:
A slightly harder sloper problem.

Start matched on the jug and move into the sidepull. Hike your feet up and desperately try to find an adequate slopey indent to put your fingers in around the bulge. Move your right hand into the fat undercling and mantel.
content.location: Second route from the left hand side. Obvious jug start

content.description: Use the crimp rail to move into a left hand gaston on a block, then move feet up and catch the undercling. From there, use the same slopey dishes to top as the V2/3
content.protection: A pad might boost some confidence on the topout
content.location: Sit start using the crimp rail underneath the undercling start for The Spider.

content.description:
Start on two underclings at about chest level.  Get your feet on and go for the jug.

The route is a one-move wonder.  If you can make the awkward throw from the undercling for the jug above, the rest of the route is V0-1.
content.protection: A pad.  The landing is nice and flat.
content.location: Start on the far right of the Baby's Got Biceps boulder.  The underclings are obvious.

content.description:
Start in the same crack in the dihedral and make a move up to a good horizontal slot. Match hands and top out.

Decent short problem to limber up on
content.location: Start in the dihedral and go straight up

content.description: Good to get warm on. Begin in the crack in the dihedral and work your way left on jugs followed by an easy top out
content.location: Start in the dihedral to the right of the tree
